Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
check_power_intent(25.10)                            check_power_intent(25.10)

Name
       check_power_intent  - Checks the IEEE1801 power intent coding style for
       the IEEE1801 partitioning

Syntax
       check_power_intent

       [-help]

       -1801

       -hierarchical

       [-outfile <string>]

       [-verbose]

       Checks the IEEE1801 power intent coding style for the  IEEE1801  parti-
       tioning.  This  command  also  reports potential IEEE1801 coding style,
       which is unsuitable for partitioning.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each check_power_intent parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man check_power_intent

       -1801  Specifies that the power intent is IEEE 1801.

       -hierarchical
              Specifies the input power intent style.

       -outfile <string>
              Specifies the output filename.

       -verbose
              Prints the detailed information related to  the  check_power_in-
              tent command.

Related Information
              * commit_power_intent

              * free_power_intent

              * read_power_intent

              * write_power_intent

              * Low Power Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

